714183f-a.title: Manhattan: 65th Street - Central Park West
714183f-a.text:
65th Street, and Central Park West. Before Reconstruction.
Lutz heater in operation.
President Borough of Manhattan.
August 21, 1918.
714183f-a.folder: 65th Street & Central Park West, Manhattan, NY

718448f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 65th Street
718448f-a.text:
North on Central Park West from 65th Street. The street is torn up for the construction of the Eighth Avenue subway. At the date of this photograph, south bound traffic only was permitted on Central Park West. Now (1935) the reverse is true.
October 29, 1928.
P. L. Sperr, Photographer.
718448f-a.folder: Central Park West & 65th Street, Manhattan, NY

718449f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 65th Street
718449f-a.text:
Church of the Holy Trinity (Evangelical Lutheran), Central Park West at N.N. corner of 65th Street.
March 11, 1929.
P. L. Sperr, Photographer.
718449f-a.folder: Central Park West & 65th Street, Manhattan, NY

718451f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 65th Street
718451f-a.text:
Central Park West, west side, from 65th to 66th Streets, from Central Park. At left is the Church of the Holy Trinity (Evangelical Lutheran).
March 11, 1929.
P. L. Sperr, Photographer.
718451f-a.folder: Central Park West & 65th Street, Manhattan, NY

718308f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 65th Street
718308f-a.text:
Central Park, Pathways, at North Meadow, and Upper Reservoir: the viow is southwest from Fifth Avenue and 100th Street, showing Central Park West from 91st to 65th Streets.
September 8, 1931.
Wurts Brothers.
718308f-a.folder: Central Park West & 65th Street, Manhattan, NY

714184f-a.title: Manhattan: 65th Street - Central Park West
714184f-a.text:
West 65th Street, south side, west from but not including Central Park West. In the background appears a portion of the Sixth Ave. Elevated line, running at this point on Columbus Ave.
March 2, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
